This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with modeling compositional structures in natural scenes. The use of deep learning and unsupervised learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions interpretability and transferability, which are important in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of scene graphs and natural language processing techniques for generating imaginary scenes suggests that it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the use of latent variable models suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
